Command syntax :
    /mode <target> [<modestring> [<mode arguments>...]]

        <target>: Either a channel name (prefixed with '#') or a user nickname
        <modestring>: Starts with '+' (add) or '-' (remove) followed by mode letters
        <mode arguments>: Additional parameters required by some modes

################################################################################################################################

Command parsing: 

    Extract targert -> extract mode string -> extract parameters -> process channel mode

################################################################################################################################


MODES:

    MODE:  |   DISCREPTION                                                | PARAM     | TYPE

     +/-i: | Set/remove Invite-only channel                               | 0         | toggle

     +/-t: | Set/remove the restrictions of the TOPIC command to channel  | none      | toggle
                operators                                                 

    +/-K:  | Set/remove the channel key (password)                        | password  | setting

    +/-O:  | Give/take channel operator privilege                         | nickname  | targeted

    +/-l:  | Set/remove the user limit to channel                         | number    | setting    
    

